author: Kelly Terez
title: Heavy Rain Floods Washington State Football Stadium
text:
Share Article 
iStock/Thinkstock (SEATTLE) -- A stadium in Washington state suddenly turned into something resembling a lake following heavy rain Saturday. 
Heavy rainfall flowed through the steps of Tacoma’s Stadium High School and into the nearby Stadium Bowl, ABC News affiliate KOMO-TV in Seattle reports. Video posted on YouTube showed the football field almost entirely covered in water. 
"I looked out my window and it was almost like a river coming down 2nd Street,” Angela Rapada told KOMO-TV. “I was like 'Oh my God! I bet you the Stadium Bowl is just crazy right now.'"
